CHAT.comment: Teaching. Mother and Child sit on living room floor. Mother first teaches Child to string bead on a shoelace. Then she teaches her to sort black and white buttons into two small boxes. Child's speech is usually intelligible.

u.a: covers Mother hand as she demonstrates , simultaneous .
pushes box of beads closer to Child .
gives string and bead to Mother .
holds it out for Child to do .
reaches to bead she has just thrown .
start to put white one in .
pours buttons from box to box .
